name: Infamy
overview: Caught between her Roma roots and pressure from her friends, a 17-year-old girl aspires to become a hip-hop musician despite her parents' strict rules.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: 17-year-old Gita reluctantly moves back to a small town in Poland after a stint in Wales and enrolls in school despite her family's objections.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: Faced with her new friends' prejudice, Gita makes up an alternative life story. Tagar flees relentless scrutiny after an incident with his dog.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Learning the truth behind her parents' plan, Gita visits her ousted sister and realizes the consequences of going against the family.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: With her friends from Wales visiting, Gita basks in their acclaim as she solidifies her double life. Viola gets advice to tackle the debt.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: Gita finds that her newfound freedom is short-lived as Marko brings her along on a business trip where Janko awaits.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: As tragedy strikes twice, Gita learns the truth about Tagar. Eliza questions her actions when confronted by the priest.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: A brutal attack sends shock waves through Biała Góra. Gita grieves by cementing a legacy while Eliza fears retribution from Mikołaj.

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: Family or infamy? An act of defiance causes a ruckus within the family, leading to merciless repercussions.
